UID:9lH4T33iZZsz786yNIEfu
SUMMARY:Summer Soccer Celebration
DTSTAMP:20260616T174851Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260620T080000
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of the world’s greatest soccer tournament playin
	g out in Houston and cities across North America\, Levy Park is getting in
	to the festivities with free game watch parties. This series of 15 curated
	\, family-friendly watch parties offers a central gathering place for fùtb
	ol fans to catch some of the tournament’s most anticipated games\, includi
	ng key matchups featuring the United States and Mexico\, as well as pivota
	l knockout rounds. Each free viewing event will feature a large-scale outd
	oor LED screen with professional sound\, entertainment\, food and beverage
	 concessions\, and merchandise sales. \nCommunity Partners: Further enhanc
	ing programming\, Levy Park will partner with local organizations to broad
	en community engagement\, including collaborations with cultural groups an
	d soccer-focused nonprofits. Levy Park is seeking enthusiastic volunteers 
	and community partner organizations to help bring this festival to life. V
	olunteers will work directly alongside our event team\, supporting booth o
	perations and helping ensure every guest has an unforgettable experience. 
	Email us to learn more about volunteer opportunities. \nFood and Beverage 
	Concessions: Enjoy a variety of festival food fare\, beer and wine\, and n
	on-alcoholic beverages from Coca-Cola. \nMerchandise: Event merchandise ce
	lebrating Houston\, Levy Park\, and the global soccer tournament will also
	 be available for purchase. \nArt Installations and Photo Opportunities: C
	ommemorate the experience with a photo tour of the park\, including life-s
	ized soccer-themed photo backdrops and a tournament bracket. Visit our soc
	cer ball music box and turn the crank for festive sounds. \nGroup Stage Fe
	stival Schedule: \nThursday\, June 11 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – Mexic
	o vs South Africa (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nFriday\, June 12 from 6:30 p.m. t
	o 11:00 p.m. – USA vs Paraguay (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nThursday\, June 18 f
	rom 6:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m. – Mexico vs South Korea (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \
	nFriday\, June 19 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – USA vs Australia (2:00 p.
	m. Kick Off) \nWednesday\, June 24 from 6:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m. – Czechia 
	vs Mexico (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nRound of 32 Festival Schedule: \nSunday\,
	 June 28 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – 2A vs 2B (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nWe
	dnesday\, July 1 from 5:30 p.m. to 10:30 p.m. – 1D vs 3BEFIJ (7:00 p.m. Ki
	ck Off) \nRound of 16 Festival Schedule: \nMonday\, July 6 from 5:30 p.m. 
	to 10:30 p.m. – W81 vs W82 (7:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nQuarter-Finals Festival 
	Schedule: \nThursday\, July 9 from 1:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m. – W89 vs W90 (3:
	00 p.m. Kick Off) \nFriday\, July 10 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – W93 vs
	 W94 (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nSaturday\, July 11 from 2:30 p.m. to 11:00 p.m
	. – W91 vs W92 (4:00 p.m. Kick Off) & W95 vs W96 (8:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nSe
	mi-Finals Festival Schedule: \nTuesday\, July 14 from 12:30 p.m. to 5:30 p
	.m. – W97 vs W98 (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nWednesday\, July 15 from 12:30 p.m
	. to 5:30 p.m. – W99 vs W100 (2:00 p.m. Kick Off) \nFinals Festival Schedu
	le: \nSaturday\, July 18 from 2:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. – Bronze Final (4:00 
	p.m. Kick Off) \nSunday\, July 19 from 12:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m. – Final (2:
	00 p.m. Kick Off)\n\nhttps://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/summer-soccer-
	celebration/\n\nFrom Levy Park Houston
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/summer-soccer-celebration/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:levy-park-houston
CATEGORIES:Levy Park Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT936H
END:VEVENT
